<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7561504>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Valdasus cerdai, n. sp. A. Habitus in dorsal view. Scale = 1 mm. B. Head in dorsal view. Scale = 0.5 mm. C. Head in frontal view. Scales = 0.5 mm. D. First antennal segment. Scale = 0.1 mm. E. Pronotum in dorsal view. F. Scutellum in dorsal view. G. Corium in dorsal view. Scales = 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7561504/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7561508>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Valdasus cerdai, n. sp. Male genital structures. A. Left paramere. B. Right paramere. C. Endophallus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7561508/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7561514>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Valdasoides bahiensis Carvalho, 1989. Male holotype from MNRJ destroyed in the fire of September 02d 2018 photographied by the first author during his last stay in Rio. Scale = 1 mm (according to Carvalho, 1989)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7561514/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

